#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Quarkus Hibernate with Panache Next renamed to Quarkus Data Hibernate"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: synopsis
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "We've renamed Quarkus Hibernate with Panache to Quarkus Data Hibernate, and are looking for feedback"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Goodbye Hibernate with Panache Next… welcome Quarkus Data Hibernate 🥳"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"It's already been a while since we introduced\n"
"xref:2025-12-24-hibernate-panache-next.asciidoc[Quarkus Hibernate with Panache Next], and since then, we've decided to\n"
"move closer to the link:https://jakarta.ee/specifications/data/1.1/jakarta-data-1.1-m3[Jakarta Data] standard, as well\n"
"as rename the module to https://quarkus.io/version/main/guides/quarkus-data-hibernate[Quarkus Data Hibernate]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"I'll repeat the original disclaimer: this is a new extension, which is experimental, which means everything\n"
"about it can (and probably will) change: the extension name, the package names, the class names\n"
"and even the API. We are releasing it because we feel it's in a good shape to be tested and discussed\n"
"by the community, and we hope to get better feedback before we commit to anything like names or\n"
"API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Please report feedback either on link:https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/187038-dev/topic/WG.20-.20Quarkus.20Data/with/598039033[Zulip]\n"
"or via link:https://github.com/orgs/quarkusio/projects/50/views/1[GitHub issues]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "What changed since last time?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Pivoted from the Panache 1\n"
"link:https://javadoc.io/doc/io.quarkus/quarkus-panache-common/latest/io/quarkus/panache/common/Sort.html[`Sort`] type\n"
"to the Jakarta Data link:https://jakarta.ee/specifications/data/1.1/apidocs/jakarta.data/jakarta/data/order[`Order`]\n"
"type for sorting: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/53429"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Supported link:https://quarkus.io/version/main/guides/hibernate-reactive-panache#transactions[`@Transactional`]\n"
"for Hibernate Reactive transactions: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/47698"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Support non-blocking link:https://quarkus.io/guides/lifecycle#startup_annotation[`@Startup`] methods:\n"
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/50175"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"The link:https://jakarta.ee/specifications/data/1.1/apidocs/jakarta.data/jakarta/data/repository/repository[`@Repository`]\n"
"annotation is now optional on nested repositories: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/50178"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Added a codestart: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/51565"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Make sure the link:https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-reactive[Hibernate Reactive] dependency is optional:\n"
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/52265"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Deprecated the link:https://javadoc.io/doc/io.quarkus/quarkus-panache-common/latest/io/quarkus/panache/common/Parameters.html[`Parameters`]\n"
"class in favour of link:https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Map.html#of()[`Map.of`]:\n"
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/52583"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Added link:https://javadoc.io/doc/io.quarkus/quarkus-hibernate-panache-next/latest/io/quarkus/hibernate/panache/stateless/PanacheStatelessEntityOperations.html#upsert()[`upsert`]\n"
"operation: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/52574"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Make `StatelessSession` injectable for link:https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-reactive[Hibernate Reactive]\n"
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/47462"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Support link:https://quarkus.io/guides/security-overview#key-features-of-quarkus-security[security annotations]\n"
"on repositories: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/53623"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Support link:https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#further-simplification-with-injectmock[`@InjectMock`]\n"
"on repositories: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/53873"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "And many other bug fixes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Need feedback"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "We're currently working on various issues, but we could especially use feedback on the following topics:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Paging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"We're switching to Jakarta Data `Page` and `PageRequest` for paging, including using cursors. This one will introduce a new\n"
"API on `PanacheQuery` for paging: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/53431"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Names"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "In https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/53145 we are considering moving:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Our package name from `io.quarkus.hibernate.panache` to `io.quarkus.data.hibernate` (this one is pretty obvious)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"The `PanacheEntity` name to `ManagedEntity` (for entities backed by a stateful session), and `RecordEntity` or\n"
"`ActiveRecord` (for entities backed by a stateless session)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "The `PanacheRepository` name to… something that would go along with whatever names we pick for our entities 😬"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Please comment on the issue if you like this or think of anything better. But please read all the discussion first :)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Automatic configuration of required annotation processor"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"On https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/53901 we have a proof of concept that lets our Maven and Gradle builds\n"
"automatically configure the required Hibernate Processor annotation processor, so that you can't forget to add them\n"
"to your builds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "This raises questions about magic and compatibility with IDEs, so chime in if you have opinions about those."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "Let us know"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid "We're still looking for feedback, and testers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-28-panache-next-renamed-to-quarkus-data.asciidoc
msgid ""
"Give it a try, https://quarkus.io/version/main/guides/quarkus-data-hibernate[read the documentation], and give us feedback either on\n"
"link:https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/187038-dev/topic/WG.20-.20Quarkus.20Data/with/598039033[Zulip]\n"
"or via link:https://github.com/orgs/quarkusio/projects/50/views/1[GitHub issues]."
msgstr ""
